#################################################################
Planet Ring DC Server
Author Shuouma
2017
#################################################################
Description
#################################################################
This is the source code release of the Planet Ring server.
It is a remake of the old server, but as always,
this is not a production release. So take it as it is.

Thanks to:
IberDC the development team in WWW.DREAMCAST.ES
- For doing the first server and all the research

#################################################################
Prerequisite & Limitations
#################################################################
1. Libraries for sqlite3 (libsqlite3) and pthread are required for compilation
2. It is mandatory to edit the planetring.cfg and replace <SERVER_IP> to the public IP of your server.
3. The code is only tested on a Little-endian (byte-order) and X86_64 architecture. Will probably not
   work on big-endian without smaller modifications of the code.
4. The release is for Linux

#################################################################
Compile & Run
#################################################################
1. make (to compile the source code)
2. Execute the binaries planetring_server
Note:
Create your own init.d scripts for easier launch. Pipe the log to file.


Happy Gaming
Shuouma